d Spanish nationalism, were a direct result of his immersion in Edwardian currents of thought. This in turn casts new light on the influence that Britain exerted over Spain during this period, and provides fresh insights into the cultural dynamics which led to the Spanish Civil War. Dr David Jiménez Torres is associate lecturer at Universidad Camilo José Cela.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJournalistszEnglandzLondonvBiography. 0aJournalistszSpainvBiography. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aModern History. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aEnglish influence.  aRamiro de Maeztu.  aSpanish history.  aSpanish journalists.  aSpanish writers.  aauthor biography.  aearly twentieth century.  ahistory.  ainternational relations.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311143131440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204837440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782048374423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782048374/original  a978-3-11-143131-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles